stork.feather

Class Transfer<S extends Resource,D extends Resource>

  • java.lang.Object
    • stork.feather.Transfer<S,D>
  • Type Parameters:
    S - the source Resource type.
    D - the destination Resource type.
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ProxyTransfer

    public abstract class Transfer<S extends Resource,D extends Resource>
extends Object
    A handle on the state of a data transfer. This class contains methods for controlling data flow and monitoring data throughput. This is the base class for ProxyTransfer as well as any custom Transfer controller.

    Control operations are performed on a Transfer through public Bell members. This allows implementors to make assumptions about what states certain control methods may be called from.

        public boolean random()
        Check if the pipeline is capable of draining Slices in arbitrary order. The return value of this method should remain constant across calls.
        Returns:
        true if transmitting slices in arbitrary order is supported.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if this method is called when the pipeline has not been initialized.

      • concurrency

        public int concurrency()
        Get the number of distinct Resources the pipeline may be in the process of transferring simultaneously.

        Returning a number less than or equal to zero indicates that an arbitrary number of Resources may be transferred concurrently.

        Returns:
        The number of data Resources this sink can receive concurrently.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if this method is called when the pipeline has not been initialized.
